data.title: Love this restaurant!
data.text: I live in downtown CL & subscribe to Kara Lynn's "Good 2 Go"  meal program. I pick up my delicious cooked Paleo meals 2xwk. They're delicious, healthy & save tons of time. Sometimes I just stop by & eat there. Everyone is very friendly & it's a cozy environment. Desserts are incredible!

data.title: Mife loved it!
data.text:
Homemade....Healthy........Tasty....Friendly staff.  What a surprise as the other places nearby are not as good.

We are going back!

data.title: Very Nice Kitchen Stir Fry
data.text: On a recent Saturday evening, I stopped in with a friend and tried the Kitchen Stir Fry which came with red cabbage, white cabbage, carrots, onions, asparagus, wok sauce topped with beef. I was pleased with the amount of beef that adorned the top of the stir fry as, unfortunately, veggies tend to leave me feeling hungry after eating. Not so with ample beef (which is a reasonable additional cost for the quantity). The combination of flavors was quite tasty for me. This stir fry is pretty much as good as it gets. In other words, I am not sure I have ever had better in a restaurant. In terms of overall rating, I cannot give Kara Lynn's more than a four for two reasons: 1) we had to go to the counter to order and pay on the spot. I prefer wait staff coming over and taking my order and paying after I have eaten; and 2) we had to get up and get water for ourselves. For some, this may seem nit-picky, but, hey, these are my preferences and I did not know, going in, that those were the house rules. I will say that there was a steady stream of people coming for take-out, another testament for the quality of the food. Will I return? Yes, on those days when I do not feel like cooking but am ok serving myself.

data.title: Tastiest Food
data.text: I think going to this place regularly for the last few years and I've never had one bad meal EVER. Everything is delicious and healthy. And for a being as healthy as it is the price is quite fair. Sometimes I can't believe this place exists in Clearwater. I feel like it's a restaurant that would exist in Los Angeles or San Francisco or New York. Love this place

data.title: Healthy Eats
data.text: Discovered this little gem of a restaurant after attending a concert at the Capital Theater in downtown Clearwater. Food is awesome and healthy. Highly recommend

data.title: Good to try
data.text: I try the lamb with Mediterranean sauce. It is awesome. Taste is very good. Juicy meat and nice sauce. It just few minutes walk from clearwater marine aquarium second facility. Must try.

data.title: Holy cow this is good!
data.text: Kara Lynn's is a paleo and vegan friendly restaurant. The food is fantastic! On Saturdays they have amazing vegan/ paleo scones that are just sweet enough to satisfy. Everything on the menu is fresh and delicious. I've really enjoyed trying a variety of menu items such as the meatloaf, turkey patties and the Korean steak wrap. I leave feeling full and fresh. The staff is amazing and very knowledgable about the food prep.

data.title: Healthy food
data.text: I was excited to find a place to eat while we were on vacation that served gluten free and paleo food. Our to-go order included the green veggie soup, quiche, bunless hotdog served with asparagus, and assorted muffins and banana bread. The food was good and I would return if visiting again, however they did mix or order up and we ended up not getting all we ordered. Also service was slow, which they were apologetic about. I would give it 3 stars, but just the very fact I could eat healthily while away from was enough for 4 stars.

data.title: Healthy Food
data.text: If you want to eat healthy at a reasonable price, Kara Lynn's Kitchen located in downtown Clearwater is the place to go.  Excellent items to select from, all fresh and a nice warm atmosphere.  You won't be disappointed and I'm sure you'll return time after time once you visit.  I've told many of my friends about Kara Lynn's and they all have been very appreciative.

data.title: Amazing...Healthy Wholesome Food Can Be Delicious Too!
data.text:
We were going to the Capital Theatre one evening and Kara Lynn's is just up the street.  We liked the clean warm look and the friendly greeting as we came in.  We both had the meatloaf dinner and it came with a choice of one of two vegetables...green beans or broccoli.  The food was delicious....mushroom gravy was not the flour and corn starch type, just clear juice, and the meatloaf was packed with various vegetables. 

Desserts looked really nice too, and we each had a chocolate and avocado pudding, with a hint of banana and it was unique and superb.

Very friendly and efficient service.  We really like this restaurant - we watch what we eat and we like Kara Lynn's top quality food and service.

data.title: Health Dining in downtown Clearwater
data.text: If you want to enjoy downtown Clearwater and have a very healthy meal that is tasty, then Kara Lynn's is a great choice.

data.title: A little price but the food is good!
data.text: Some people that I know rave about this place, I think the food is good but a little pricey. Also, I don't need a war and peace dissertation to explain to me the life cycle of the 4 oz. steak you're about to serve me for $12. I feel like I should be listening to contemporary jazz and discussing 14th century french poetry to dine here. Hipsters are welcome and encouraged to attend.

data.title: Fresh, Healthy and Vegan-Freindly
data.text: Stumbled upon this amazing restaurant and couldn't have been happier. All the ingredients are organic or on the "clean list" and while the focus is paleo, the vegan options are outstanding.  My minestrone was loaded with seasonal veggies and the KLK's Organic Quinoa Salad was fresh and filling.

data.title: Freshest Ingredients
data.text: Many gluten free savory muffins like carrot and blueberry. Salads feature quinoe. Wonderful quiche. Daily soups like pure blended vegetable or a spicy Italian sausage vegetable with slices not dices. Bright cheerful decor. Friendly staff including owner works the floor.

data.title: Good food and its good for you
data.text: Its nice to be able to go to a place with clean food - and where you know there isn't going to be any junk in it.Everything is made by hand and it really tastes good. Better than you'd expect for a healthy restaurant. The food is a little heavier on the garlic as its a good anti-inflammatory - but you can always find something that isn't. Highly recommended.

data.title: Incredible Organic Gluten Free Food!
data.text: We have been eating there for a while fantastic food - husband loves it and we also are on their weekly good to go program!

data.title: Fantastic Ceviche!
data.text: I had the ceviche for lunch a couple of days ago and I'm still remembering it, so I figured I'd better post a recommendation!  It was perfectly seasoned, tender and DELICIOUS - especially in the heat!  I have eaten here before, and have NEVER had a bad meal, so I highly recommend it!  Perfect for those who want to eat ORGANIC, HOMESTYLE food.

data.title: Loved it!!
data.text: I was just walking around Clearwater and spotted Kara Lynns.  The special on the board drew me in (Salmon) and WOW... not only did I have one of the best meals ever; I took food to go.  I can't wait to go back to Clearwater so I can eat there again!

data.title: Delicious, High Quality "Good for You" Menu Choices!
data.text: Each time I visit Kara Lynn's Kitchen I am wowed!  They have varied menu choices and use organic fruits and vegetables and grain fed meats and poultry. Their Quiche Lorraine or Veggie Quiche won't disappoint you and it is served with a side salad or cup of soup.  The soups are tasty too. If you need to follow a gluten free meal plan or are on the Paleo diet then this is an added benefit. Kara Lynn's is a great place to go before a show at the Capitol Theatre.  Try their famous Carrot Muffins and their Chocolate Pudding made with avocados - both of these are amazing! And the service is great as well. p.s. - I understand you can also have them cook meals for you weekly.

data.title: Gluten free & paleo dining
data.text: We have walked by many times and finally walked in. What a surprise! Kara makes 2 entrées daily. Gluten free, paleo cuisine. I had her pork tenderloin with broccoli. My guest had meatloaf which had onion and spinach. It was the best meatloaf I've ever had. They even serve mint infused water. You can text her your order, take it home. We will be regulars.
